  "local_port": 58664,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you deposit cash at an ATM?",
  "response": "Depositing cash at an ATM is generally a straightforward process. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide:\n\n1. **Find an ATM**: Locate an ATM that allows cash deposits. Look for ATMs associated with your bank or one that specifies it accepts cash deposits.\n\n2. **Insert Your Card**: Insert your debit or ATM card into the machine. If it has a card reader, follow the prompts to access your account.\n\n3. **Enter Your PIN**: Enter your Personal Identification Number (PIN) when prompted to authenticate yourself.\n\n4. **Choose Deposit Option**: Select the option for depositing cash. This might be labeled differently depending on the ATM, such as \u201cDeposit,\u201d \u201cCash Deposit,\u201d or \u201cCheck/Cash Deposit.\u201d\n\n5. **Select Account**: If prompted, choose the account where you want the cash to be deposited (e.g., checking, savings).\n\n6. **Prepare Cash**: Ensure your cash is flat and free of any foreign objects. Most ATMs will not accept crumpled or damaged bills.\n\n7. **Insert Cash**: Follow the on-screen instructions for inserting cash. Some ATMs have a slot where you can deposit multiple bills at once, while others may require you to insert them one by one.\n\n8. **Confirm Amount**: After inserting the bills, the ATM may display the total amount. Confirm that it is correct.\n\n9. **Complete Transaction**: Follow the instructions to complete the transaction. The ATM will usually provide a receipt that confirms the deposit.\n\n10. **Take Your Card and Receipt**: Make sure to take your debit card and any receipt the ATM provides before leaving.\n\nKeep in mind that processing times for cash deposits can vary, so check your bank's policies regarding immediate availability of funds. Also, ensure that you are in a secure and well-lit area when performing the transaction.",
